---
/**
 * storage-engines · storage-engines-fundamentals · Figure 7 — Level 7, the
 * cost migrating from read time to write time as you denormalize.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source page (figure + svg + figcaption). References
 * marker-end="url(#arw)", so the grey #arw marker is inlined here in a local
 * <defs> (verbatim from the source defs block) so it resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The cost migrates from read time to write time as you denormalize"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="140"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">NORMALIZED</text
            >
            <text
                x="420"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">DENORMALIZED</text
            >
            <rect x="36" y="36" width="100" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect><text x="86" y="53" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5">customers (1×)</text>
            <rect x="36" y="78" width="100" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect><text x="86" y="95" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5">orders → FK</text>
            <line x1="86" y1="78" x2="86" y2="64" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="140" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >read = JOIN</text
            >
            <text x="140" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >change = 1 update</text
            >
            <line x1="270" y1="10" x2="270" y2="140" stroke="#d8d4c8" stroke-dasharray="4 4"></line>
            <g font-size="9.5">
                <rect x="316" y="36" width="208" height="22" rx="5" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect><text x="420" y="51" text-anchor="middle">order #1 + customer copy</text>
                <rect x="316" y="64" width="208" height="22" rx="5" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect><text x="420" y="79" text-anchor="middle">order #2 + customer copy</text>
                <rect x="316" y="92" width="208" height="22" rx="5" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect><text x="420" y="107" text-anchor="middle">order #3 + customer copy</text>
            </g>
            <text x="420" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >read = single row</text
            >
            <text x="420" y="143" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >change = fan-out update (the update anomaly)</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Denormalization doesn't remove the consistency problem — it moves it into your application
        and transactions (or a materialized view).
    </figcaption>
</figure>
